Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{120%grams}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Transfer half the beans to a #medium bowl{} and mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%grams}. Zest and cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

In a medium bowl, combine the @olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the salsa), half the lime juice and a pinch of @sugar{1%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add the tomatoes, toss to coat, then set aside.

Spread the @McCain Home Chips{400%grams} on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%grams} and season with salt and pepper. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add half the @tomato puree{60%grams} and cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the whole and mashed black beans, @chipotle paste{20%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), the sugar and @water{100%ml}(for the chicken) and half the @chicken stock paste{20%grams}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{6} on a #board{} (2 per person). Spoon the chicken and black bean filling down the centre of each, then roll them up to enclose the filling.

Drizzle a little oil over the bottom of a large #ovenproof dish{}, then lay in the wraps. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge underneath so they don't unroll. Sprinkle over two thirds of the cheese.

Cut the remaining tortillas into triangles (use #scissors{} if easier). Place on a large baking tray in a single layer and drizzle with oil. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Bake the enchiladas and tortilla chips on the middle shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British beef mince{240%grams} and fry until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and discard any excess fat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Mexican style spice mix{1%sachet} and remaining tomato puree. Fry, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @honey{1%tbsp}, @water{100%ml}(for the beef), a squeeze of lime juice and the remaining chicken stock paste. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt, pepper and more lime juice if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Place the chips in a #serving bowl{} and top with the spiced beef. Sprinkle over the remaining cheese and a pinch of lime zest.

Plate up the enchiladas and drizzle over half the @soured cream{150%grams}.

Serve the tomato salsa, @smashed avocado{1%pot} and remaining soured cream alongside. Mix the remaining lime zest with the soured cream if you'd like to.

Serve with the tortilla chips for dipping.

Enjoy!